I&#39;ve had a slight change of heart regarding the structure of a possible 
standard NEAT XML dialect. Potentially I&#39;m being a bit over ambitious 
here but see what you think. This is basically a superset of everything 
that has been mentioned so far, and as such can be reduced via XSLT to 
any of the other formats (Derek&#39;s and Ken&#39;s) that have been mentioned.

Jim, generally I agree with you regarding the use of shortened tag 
names, but then I found myself defining a &lt;connection-mutation-rate&gt; tag 
and this seems a little over the top to me. I would say that so long as 
the name or mnemonic chosen is instantly understandable with a little 
knowledge of the context then that is fine.

I have defined 2 dialects, although they share some structure -  a 
&#39;neat-run-config&#39; that can be used to initialise a neat run, and a 
&#39;neat-run-output&#39; that represents the output from a run. Hopefully yahoo 
groups wont mangle the formatting too much...


&lt;neat-run-config&gt;

   &lt;neat-run-info&gt;
      &lt;author&gt;Mr Foo Bar&lt;/author&gt;
      &lt;description&gt;Experiment to determine relationship between 
connection-mut-rate and complexification. Test run 1 of 10&lt;/description&gt;
   &lt;/neat-run-info&gt;

   &lt;search-parameters&gt;
      &lt;pop-size&gt;10&lt;/pop-size&gt;
      &lt;neuron-mut-rate&gt;0.02&lt;/neuron-mut-rate&gt;
      &lt;connect-mut-rate&gt;0.04&lt;/connect-mut-rate&gt;
      &lt;weigth-mut-rate&gt;0.75&lt;/weight-mut-rate&gt;
      &lt;survival-rate&gt;0.1&lt;/survival-rate&gt;
   &lt;/search-parameters&gt;

   &lt;end-condition&gt;
         &lt;!-- optional end conditions. If more than one specified then 
terminate on whichever is true first --&gt;
         &lt;max-generations&gt;100&lt;/max-generations&gt;
         &lt;fitness-threshold type=&quot;ceiling||floor&quot;&gt;123&lt;/fitness-threshold&gt;
         &lt;clocktime type=&quot;absolute||duration&quot;&gt;2004-02-24 23:00 || 
1:00&lt;/clocktime&gt;
   &lt;/end-condition&gt;

   &lt;environment-config&gt;
      &lt;environment-id id=&quot;DereksTicTacToe_variation99&quot; version=&quot;1.01&quot; 
authoreddate=&quot;01/01/2004&quot;&gt;Derek&#39;s Implemetation of a Tic-Tac-Toe 
environment&lt;/environment-id&gt;

      &lt;environment-parameters&gt;
         &lt;input-node-count&gt;10&lt;&lt;input-node-count&gt;
         &lt;output-node-count&gt;10&lt;output-node-count&gt;
      &lt;/environment-parameters&gt;
   &lt;/environment-config&gt;

   &lt;output-config&gt;
      &lt;output-level level=&quot;statsonly || full || bestgenome || 
bestgenomeperspecies || fullatend&quot;/&gt;
      &lt;per-n-generations&gt;1&lt;/per-n-generations&gt;
      &lt;per-clocktime&gt;00:01&lt;/perclocktime&gt;
   &lt;/output-config&gt;

&lt;/neat-run-config&gt;


&lt;neat-run-output&gt;

   &lt;neat-run-info&gt;
      &lt;author&gt;Mr Foo Bar&lt;/author&gt;
      &lt;description&gt;Experiment to determine relationship between 
connection-mut-rate and complexification. Test run 1 of 10&lt;/description&gt;

      &lt;!-- environment id copied from environment-config section of 
neat-run-config xml --&gt;
      &lt;environment-id id=&quot;DereksTicTacToe_variation99&quot; version=&quot;1.01&quot; 
authoreddate=&quot;01/01/2004&quot;&gt;Derek&#39;s Implemetation of a Tic-Tac-Toe 
environment&lt;/environment-id&gt;

      &lt;!-- keep track of innov num in case we wish to restart the run? --&gt;
      &lt;max-innovation-id&gt;12345&lt;/max-innovation-id&gt;
   &lt;/neat-run-info&gt;

   &lt;search-parameters&gt;
      &lt;pop-size&gt;10&lt;/pop-size&gt;
      &lt;neuron-mut-rate&gt;0.02&lt;/neuron-mut-rate&gt;
      &lt;connect-mut-rate&gt;0.04&lt;/connect-mut-rate&gt;
      &lt;weigth-mut-rate&gt;0.75&lt;/weight-mut-rate&gt;
      &lt;survival-rate&gt;0.1&lt;/survival-rate&gt;
   &lt;/search-parameters&gt;

   &lt;!-- The dialect allows for outputting all generations, just the last 
one or a subset of all generations --&gt;
   &lt;generation id=&quot;1&quot;&gt;
      &lt;generation-info&gt;
         &lt;save-time&gt;&quot;2004-02-24 00:00:12&quot;&lt;/save-time&gt;
